I bought art feom Next Street Gallery of Modus in Place des Voges and had it shipped to Italy. Shipping was very late and the artwork arrived without the wooden crate we agreed on. Luckily undeamaged. I was promised 2 catalogues of the artist, but givem only one. The gallery managers does not respond to messages to resolvw the problem. It has been over 2 months now. Not a professional behaviour.

Such an amazing gallery in Paris! This gallery is exclusively dedicated to street and urban artists. They had works from Martin Whatson, Snik, Kurar, Os Gemeos and even Banksy! The often organize openings and late night sessions, not to miss in the city. Una divertida galeria de arte dedicada en exclusiva al arte urbano y street art en Paris.
An incredible art gallery!! I highly suggest to both locals and tourists. It is a very well curated street art collection, and it is located along the beautiful Place des Vosges.

The Musee du Quai Branly is part of a two stop afternoon near Eiffel Tower. This is a beautifully presented collection of art from many cultures with quality works presented impeccably. The staff and museum guards are helpful and FRIENDLY! I had more than a couple nice conversations about the art with staff that cared about the art and helping you make a connection to the collections.

Surprising place where they exhibit urban art, their pieces are impressive and colorful. If you like this artistic trend you will really enjoy this gallery. The young woman treated us very kindly.

Good morning Thank you for your response. And what do you think about turning off your lights as soon as your store closes, especially the very powerful lights (halogen?) that illuminate the exterior wall? Some galleries on the square, for example, only light the works on display and with LEDs. ---- Hello, I could see when passing your store that the lights were on, even after closing. However, since October 2022, it has been illegal to leave a window or commercial sign lit after 1 a.m. This is due to the energy crisis we are going through and which has a direct impact on our climate. Therefore, I invite you to turn off your lights in order to respect the law, but also to help save our planet. If everyone does their part, it will have a positive impact on our collective carbon footprint.

A showcase at the cutting edge of current street art bringing together historical figures and some of the most promising young artists. Furthermore, and the icing on the cake, we find well-chosen works by great masters of modern and contemporary art: Warhol, Vasarely, Wesselmann, Combas to name a few. Special mention also for the welcome and advice, again
